com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message

Class HttpSetupMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpBaseMessage
      • com.intel.icecp.module.httpbridge.message.HttpSetupMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intel.icecp.core.Message, OnCommandMessage<HttpBridge_Module>, Serializable

    public class HttpSetupMessage
extends HttpBaseMessage
    This message is the first message sent to the module, to setup your Http Request. The setup message creates a connection and returns to you the channels to use for the actual Http request.

    Send Message

    Create a new HttpSetupMessage( returnCmdChannelURI ) passing in the required URI for the return channel. The connectionURL is also required and it represents where the Http request will be sent (eg, example: https://eap-tst.intel.com). The optional proxy parameters can be specified too. Once all the parameters are filled in, publish this message on the HttpBaseMessage.HTTP_CMD_CHANNEL_NAME channel. The results will be published on the returnCmdChannelURI channel.

    Results

    The same HttpSetupMessage is returned on the command return channel with the following filled in.

    status - The HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS of the call. If not HTTP_BRIDGE_STATUS.OK, connectionId is invalid.

    connectionId - This unique id is returned. Use this for all subsequent commands.

    dataCmdChannelURI - The URI to send HttpDataMessage commands.

    dataCmdReturnChannelURI - The URI to receive HttpDataMessage status messages.
